From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: VyOS LS1046A CI <ci@vyos-ls1046a>
Date: Sun, 08 Jun 2026 18:10:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fman_port: add dormant fman_port_set_cc_base() RX coarse-
 classification base primitive (M3-3b keystone, write mechanism, no caller)

M3-3b (per-flow exact-match RX FQ steering, spec sec 13) requires binding
an FMan RX BMI port to the root of a Coarse-Classification (CC) tree so
that, after the Parser hands frames to KeyGen, the matched key drives a
CONT_LOOKUP into the static CC tree installed by patch 0098 and the frame
is enqueued onto the per-flow RX FQ named in the matching CC action
descriptor. Sourcing the NXP SDK (FM/Port/fm_port.c FM_PORT_SetPCD,
fm_port.c:1256/1278) against mainline 6.18 established the single missing
hardware link:

  The port->KeyGen->CC routing has TWO halves. The Parser->KeyGen half is
  ALREADY wired: fman_port_use_kg_hash() (fman_port.c:1511, exported,
  already called by the AF_XDP RSS path at fman_port_init) writes
  fmbm_rfpne = NIA_ENG_HWK so frames leave the Parser for KeyGen. The
  KeyGen->CC half is the BMI "Rx Coarse Classification Base" register
  fmbm_rccb (struct fman_port_rx_bmi_regs, fman_port.c:188). grep across
  mainline confirms fmbm_rccb is NEVER written by any mainline code path
  -- it stays 0 -- which is precisely why the M2/M3 static CC tree (0098)
  installs into MURAM but never receives frames: the port has no pointer
  to the tree root, so KeyGen's CC_EN scheme mode has nowhere to dispatch.

Encoding (authoritative, SDK fm_port.c:1256/1278 + sdk_fm_cc.c
FmPcdCcBindTree:5784): the value programmed into fmbm_rccb is the RAW
MURAM byte offset of the CC tree root --
ccTreePhysOffset = XX_VirtToPhys(ccTreeBaseAddr) - physicalMuramBase --
with NO >>4 shift. (The >>4 applies only to AD next-pointers encoded
INSIDE a CONT_LOOKUP descriptor, not to the port's tree-root base.) So
the caller passes the CC tree's MURAM group offset directly; patch 0098's
struct fman_pcd_cc_tree.group_off is exactly that value (a sibling getter
lands alongside this primitive's productive consumer).

Surveying mainline 6.18.33 confirms there is NO exported API to set a
live RX port's CC base: struct fman_port and its bmi_regs are private to
fman_port.c, and fmbm_rccb has no writer at all. This patch lands the
durable in-tree WRITE primitive, DORMANT:

  int fman_port_set_cc_base(struct fman_port *port, u32 cc_muram_off);

It validates a non-NULL RX port and iowrite32be()s @cc_muram_off into
port->bmi_regs->rx.fmbm_rccb. That is the entire keystone hardware write:
once a caller passes the MURAM offset of the 0098 CC tree root, KeyGen's
CC-mode scheme (the attach_cc CCOBASE/CCBS half landing in 0097) will
dispatch matched frames into the tree and per-flow steering becomes
productive.

Why land it dormant now, with NO caller: it mirrors the exact cadence
every prior FMan offload primitive followed on this board --
fman_hm_node_install (0090), fman_policer_install (0091), and
fman_port_set_rx_bpool (0102) all shipped as exported entry points with
no productive caller before their consumers landed. A reviewable,
compiled, EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL'd primitive with zero call sites is the
standard de-risking step here. The productive call site (invoke
fman_port_set_cc_base() with fman_pcd_cc_tree.group_off, ordered FIRST in
the SetPCD sequence per SDK FM_PORT_SetPCD, then bind the KeyGen CC-mode
scheme) is the DUT-gated final sub-increment.

Why this is byte-identical to mainline on every flavor: the symbol is
exported but called by nobody in this patch, so fmbm_rccb is never
written. The RX/TX datapaths and fman_port_init() are untouched. `nm`
will show the export; the running kernel behaves exactly as the 0104b
build does.

Spec sec 13 (M3-3b CC steering keystone), fmbm_rccb WRITE primitive.

Signed-off-by: VyOS LS1046A CI <ci@vyos-ls1046a>
---
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_port.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_port.c
index 5248fe3..0fdad72 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_port.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_port.c
@@ -1520,6 +1520,46 @@ void fman_port_use_kg_hash(struct fman_port *port, bool enable)
 }
 EXPORT_SYMBOL(fman_port_use_kg_hash);
 
+/**
+ * fman_port_set_cc_base() - set a live RX port's Coarse-Classification base
+ * @port: the FMan RX port (mac_dev->port[RX])
+ * @cc_muram_off: the RAW MURAM byte offset of the CC tree root, i.e.
+ *	  patch 0098 struct fman_pcd_cc_tree.group_off (NO >>4 shift; the
+ *	  >>4 applies only to AD next-pointers inside a CONT_LOOKUP, not to
+ *	  this port-level tree-root base -- SDK fm_port.c:1256/1278).
+ *
+ * M3-3b keystone (patch 0105): the WRITE half of port->KeyGen->CC routing
+ * (spec sec 13). Programs the BMI "Rx Coarse Classification Base" register
+ * fmbm_rccb, which mainline NEVER writes (it stays 0, leaving the 0098
+ * static CC tree unreachable). After this write, frames that KeyGen
+ * dispatches in CC mode (the attach_cc CCOBASE/CCBS scheme half, patch
+ * 0097) walk the CC tree rooted at @cc_muram_off and enqueue onto the
+ * per-flow RX FQ named in the matching CC action descriptor.
+ *
+ * The Parser->KeyGen half is independent and already wired by
+ * fman_port_use_kg_hash() (fmbm_rfpne = NIA_ENG_HWK).
+ *
+ * DORMANT as of 0105 (exported, no caller). The productive call site is
+ * the DUT-gated final sub-increment: it must run FIRST in the SetPCD
+ * sequence (SDK FM_PORT_SetPCD order: bind CC tree -> write fmbm_rccb ->
+ * bind KeyGen schemes) and pass fman_pcd_cc_tree.group_off.
+ *
+ * Returns 0 on success, -EINVAL on a NULL or non-RX port.
+ */
+int fman_port_set_cc_base(struct fman_port *port, u32 cc_muram_off)
+{
+	if (!port || port->port_type != FMAN_PORT_TYPE_RX)
+		return -EINVAL;
+
+	iowrite32be(cc_muram_off, &port->bmi_regs->rx.fmbm_rccb);
+
+	dev_info(port->dev,
+		 "fman_port: RX coarse-classification base set to MURAM off 0x%x\n",
+		 cc_muram_off);
+	return 0;
+}
+EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(fman_port_set_cc_base);
+
 /**
  * fman_port_init
  * @port:	A pointer to a FM Port module.
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_port.h b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_port.h
index 9160c95..89143ba 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_port.h
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_port.h
@@ -156,4 +156,14 @@ struct device *fman_port_get_device(struct fman_port *port);
  */
 u32 fman_port_get_liodn(struct fman_port *port);
 
+/* M3-3b keystone (patch 0105): set a live RX port's Coarse-Classification
+ * base register fmbm_rccb to the RAW MURAM byte offset of the CC tree root
+ * (patch 0098 fman_pcd_cc_tree.group_off, NO >>4). This is the port->CC
+ * WRITE half of CC steering (spec sec 13); the Parser->KeyGen half is wired
+ * by fman_port_use_kg_hash(). DORMANT as of 0105 (exported, no caller); the
+ * productive call site (ordered FIRST in SetPCD, before the KeyGen CC-mode
+ * scheme bind) is the DUT-gated final sub-increment.
+ */
+int fman_port_set_cc_base(struct fman_port *port, u32 cc_muram_off);
+
 #endif /* __FMAN_PORT_H */
